slidelink.displaytext: Explain what debt security is and why companies or government issues debt securities.
Explain the direct and indirect ways in which an investor could invest money in the real estate industry.
Explain how investing in shares can produce returns.
Differentiate the trade-offs between income and growth-oriented investments.
What would be the best of the three investment portfolios listed below? Explain your response.
Explain how the portfolio you choose might fare in a bear market as opposed to a bull one.
As a financial advisor, describe how Ken and Risa will be able to pay for their daily expenses if their investment's value declines by 25% in a single year.
1. Which among the asset classes is rank as number 1 in terms of the annual returns for the FY 2021?
2. Which among the asset classes has the lowest rank in terms of the annual returns for the FY 2021?

Australian Shares Australian Property Australian Bonds
